title: Update on monitoring COVID-19 vaccination
content_text: As at 8pm on July 11, over 4.39 million doses of COVID-19 vaccines had been administered for members of the public. Around 2.59 million people had received at least one dose of vaccine, accounting for 38.1 per cent of the population aged 12 or above. The DH received 4 210 reports (Note 1) of adverse events (0.10 per cent of the total vaccine doses administered). Among the death cases concerning persons who had been vaccinated, including 25 cases (Note 2) with vaccination within 14 days before they passed away (0.0006

(Note 2) with vaccination within 14 days before they passed away (0.0006 per cent of the total vaccine doses administered), none of the death cases was associated with vaccination. As at July 11, the Expert Committee on Clinical Events Assessment Following COVID-19 Immunisation had concluded that 13 death cases had no causal relationship with vaccination, and preliminarily considered that 10 cases were not associated with vaccination. The two remaining cases were pending assessment. The Expert Committee considered that there is no unusual pattern identified so far, and will continue to closely monitor the relevant situation and collect data for assessment. According to information from the HA, during the period from June 14 to July 11, the ratio of death cases out of those without a vaccination record was 68.6 cases for every 100 000 people, whereas the ratio of death cases for those with a vaccination record was 3.0 cases for every 100 000 people. The overall death rate is similar to that recorded in the past three years. Out of those without a vaccination record, the ratio of death cases with acute stroke or acute myocardial infarction was

Furthermore, the ratio of miscarriage cases out of those without a vaccination record was 23.8 cases for every 100 000 people, whereas the ratio of miscarriage cases for those who had a vaccination record was 4.4 cases for every 100 000 people. The majority of non-death cases of adverse events received so far are relatively minor cases. week till 11.59pm on July 11, the DH received two death reports involving individuals who had received COVID-19 vaccines within 14 days before passing away. The first case involved a 52-year-old male who had received the Sinovac COVID-19 vaccine. There is no clinical evidence that the incident arose from vaccination. According to clinical information and preliminary autopsy findings, the cause of death was coronary heart disease. The second case involved a 34-year-old male who had received the BioNTech COVID-19 vaccine. There is no clinical evidence that the incident arose from vaccination.
